      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JACK JACK (2) boasts a consistent overall record including five wins from nine starts, but missed the frame latest when fourth (30.11) over 520m at Richmond. Performs well off this draw. Looks well placed here and should prove hard to beat again. PRINCE ROLEX (3) turned in a moderate effort last time when seventh at this track over 324m behind Despicable Rambo (18.47) in a Grade 4. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Worth another chance. TEN BOB NOTE (1) had a wide draw last time when running fourth (22.93) over 400m at The Gardens in a Grade 5. Boasts two wins from three starts out of this box. Key player if finds best. PRINCE LEGACY (4) was strongly fancied but finished second last time (19.88) at Goulburn, bringing a two-run winning streak to an end. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw.",
